title: kanojo_no_carrera
body:
A [[car]] focused manga series by [[Kikuchi Michitaka]]. The series follows [[Todoroki Reina]], a woman who initially knows nothing about cars, but plunges headfirst into the world of exotic sports cars upon inheriting her late father's [[porsche 964|964]] [[Porsche 911]].

The series originally ran from 2004 to 2012 and has been followed up with several sequels:

* Kanojo no Carrera RS 0 (2013)
* [[Kanojo no Carrera RS]] (2013 - 2015)
* [[Kanojo no Carrera GT3]] (2018 - present)

In addition to the sequels, the series also had a spinoff manga titled [b]Zero Angel ~Souheki no Datenshi~[/b] that ran from 2016 to 2018.

The original run was later rereleased digitally as [b]Kanojo no Carrera EV[/b]. The first 10 volumes of the rerelease have been licensed and released digitally in English as [b]My Favorite Carrera EV[/b] on "Manga Planet":[https://mangaplanet.com/comic/5dca46af44f90].

JS [i]Taigei[/i] (SS-513), the name ship of the [[Japan Maritime Self-Defense Force]]'s Taigei-class attack [[submarine]]s. Laid down at the Mitsubishi Heavy Industries Kobe Shipyard, it was named at its launch on October 14, 2020 and is scheduled to be turned over to the Maritime Self-Defense Force in 2022.

News of the submarine's launch prompted fan artists to dress the [i][[Kantai Collection]][/i] [[personification]] of its [[name connection]], [[taigei (kancolle)|a WWII submarine tender]], the same way that game depicts its submarines -- wearing a [[school swimsuit]].

title: pps-43
body:
The [b]PPS-43[/b] (Пистолет-пулемёт Судаева) is a [b][[submachine gun]][/b] chambered in 7.62×25mm Tokarev, developed by Alexei Sudayev as an alternative to the PPSh-41 with lower manufacturing cost and lower rate of fire. The [[gun]] has open-bolt blowback mechanism, predominant sheet metal parts, a pistol grip, and a top-[[folding stock]]. The magazines of both [[weapon]]s are not interchangeable.

The PPS-43 and its variants were used extensively by the Soviet forces during World War II and were later adopted by post-war militaries of several communist/socialist countries.

title: scion_tc
body:
An entry level [[sports car]] produced by [[Scion (company)|]] from 2004 to 2016. Despite being built in Japan, they were never sold in the domestic market. tCs were rebadged as the [b]Toyota Zelas[/b] in the Middle East, China, and South America staring in 2011.

While it's first two years of production were concurrent with the last two years of the [[Toyota Celica t230|T230 Celica]], the tC was considered a spiritual successor to the [[Toyota Celica|Celica]] line as it's low price point and front wheel drive format placed it in a similar market space.

title: toyota_celica_t230
body:
The seventh (and final) generation of the [[Toyota Celica]], produced from 1999 to 2006. This model was notorious for its aggressive [[sports car]] styling, as it actually had a fairly underpowered engine under the hood.

While there has been no direct successor to the T230, the [[Scion tC]] (which began production towards the end of the T230's run) is generally considered a spiritual successor.

title: marussia
body:
A now-defunct Russian [[sports car]] manufacturer founded in 2007. Primarily known for their [[Formula One]] efforts, Marussia was the first Russian automobile company to produce a supercar, but was ultimately disbanded in 2014.

Before closing, Marussia produced two road cars, the [[marussia b1|B1]] and the [[marussia B2|B2]]. A [[marussia b3|B3]] concept was designed and a prototype was partially built, but was never officially announced or brought to production. The F2, an [[sports utility vehicle|SUV]] intended for both civilian and military use, was unveiled as a concept car in 2010, but was canceled the next year.

title: multiple_monochrome
body:
An image which is composed of multiple [[monochrome]] subsections, each using a different color.

A common example would be an image in which multiple characters are each drawn using only one color thematically appropriate to them. 

Avoid applying this tag unless each character or distinct object in question could, standing alone, be tagged [[monochrome]]. However, this tag can apply to part of an image if the tag holds true for that part (e.g. the background of post #580199). 

If the each subsection is heavily themed on a single color without being monochrome, it's [[color coordination]], such as post #6313320.

It's sometimes arranged in a [[column lineup]] format. 

For spots of differing color on the same monochrome character, see [[spot color]].

title: danmaku_comments
body:
Otherwise known as scrolling comments, [i]danmaku[/i] comments (not to be confused with our actual [[danmaku]] tag) refer to the unique commenting system created by [[Niconico]]. Later also adapted by other sites such as [[AcFun]] and [[Bilibili]] (despite NND's owners owning the patent for it, due to a legal loophole). 

Danmaku comments are displayed as floating text that scrolls over the video, from right to left. This leads to comments flooding the screen ala danmaku when users react to big moments. title: i_am_a_surgeon_(meme)
body:
A meme based on the medical tv show, [[The Good Doctor]] . 

In Season 2, Episode 17 titled "Breakdown", the protagonist Dr. Shaun Murphy (played by Freddie Highmore) confronts the new Chief of Surgery, Dr. Jackson Han (played by Daniel Dae Kim), after learning Dr. Han is transferring him from Surgery to Pathology against Shaun's wishes due to Dr. Han's bigotry against autistic people despite Shaun and his co-workers proving to Dr. Han that Shaun is a great and smart doctor despite his autism. When Dr. Han still refuses to reverse his decision, Shaun has a breakdown, angrily telling Dr. Han, "[b]I am a Surgeon![/b]" repeatedly.

The scene became a popular meme in 2023 on TikTok due to how over the top Freddie Highmore's acting in that clip. Furthermore, due to many not understanding the scene out-of-context, many sided with Dr. Han, believing he had the right to remove Dr. Shaun from Surgery due to the latter's immature reaction, not realizing that Dr. Han was the antagonist and unfairly removed Dr. Shaun from Surgery due to Dr. Han's bigotry against autistic people.

title: call_of_duty:_world_at_war
body:
A first-person shooter [[video game]] developed by [[Treyarch]] and published by [[Activision]]. The game was released in November 2008 and is the fifth installment in the [[Call of Duty]] franchise. World at War is set during [[World War II]] and features both single-player and multiplayer modes.

The single-player campaign mostly follows the perspectives of two different Allied soldiers: Private Miller of the [[United States Marine Corps]] and Private Dimitri Petrenko of the [[Soviet Army]]. The game's story takes place in the Pacific and Eastern Front theaters of World War II, with players fighting against Japanese and German forces.

It was also the first game to introduce the [[zombie|Zombies]] gamemode, formerly known as Nazi Zombies during the game's lifespan.

World at War was generally well-received by critics and fans, with many praising the game's gritty depiction of World War II and its intense gameplay.

title: kurt_cobain
body:
An American musician, best known as the lead singer, guitarist, and primary songwriter of the rock band [[nirvana (band)|Nirvana]]. Born on February 20, 1967, in Aberdeen, Washington, he started playing music at a young age. In 1987, he formed Nirvana with bassist [[Krist Novoselic]], with drummer [[Dave Grohl]] eventually joining in 1990, after a succession of a few others in the position.

Nirvana's second album, "[[Nevermind]]," was released in 1991 and featured the hit single "Smells Like Teen Spirit," which helped to popularize the grunge music genre. Despite his success, Cobain struggled with drug addiction, chronic pain, and depression throughout his life, and tragically died by suicide on April 5, 1994, at the age of 27.

title: demon_days_(gorillaz)
body:
The second studio album by the British virtual band Gorillaz, released in 2005. The album features a diverse range of musical styles, including alternative rock, hip-hop, electronic, and pop, and features collaborations with a number of high-profile artists, including De La Soul, MF Doom, Neneh Cherry, and Ike Turner.

The album is known for its dark, apocalyptic themes and commentary on modern society, with lyrics that address topics such as war, politics, and consumer culture. The album's sound is characterized by its use of electronic beats, samples, and synthesizers, as well as the distinctive vocal style of Gorillaz frontman Damon Albarn.

"Demon Days" was a critical and commercial success upon its release, and has since become one of the band's most popular and well-regarded albums. It features several hit singles, including "Feel Good Inc.", "DARE", and "Dirty Harry", and was nominated for several awards, including the Grammy Award for Best Alternative Music Album.

It is also a source for parodies based off [[album cover redraw|album cover redraws]].

h4. External links

One of the Bosses from [[Metal Slug]], Specifically from Metal Slug 1 and Metal Slug X.

Karn is one of the pair of super-heavy tanks (the other one is Shoe, its twin.)  created by the Rebel Army for cooperative mission. They are each armed with one main turret-mounted cannon, two sub-cannon turrets on the front, and a missile launcher on the back. Two side-mounted hatches allow soldiers to help defend the tank as well, usually with bazookas or rocket launchers.

In the game itself, Karn fires an HE cannon and HEAT Rounds from its sub turrets, combined with a Rocket Howitzer launching from its rear. The differences is Karn is using a darker or lighter color than Shoe, while the rest of its armaments are identical.

Normally she wears common [[miko]] clothing (from serving the Kagurazaki miko family for generations) along with her yellowish [[blonde hair]] and [[red eyes]]. She is prone to entering "half-demon form," however, by popping her [[fox tail|tail]][[multiple tails|(s)]], [[claws]], and [[fox ears|ears]] whenever emotional or agitated. 

Often seen with [[ujikintoki tamaryu|Tamaryu]] and later [[ran straherz|Ran]], having her crush on the former expand into outright polygynous engagement with the whole love triangle.

After being tapped by the Kuuko [[Saiguuji Sachi|Sachi]] to be a successor in the "Holy Trio" (as "Radiant Heaven Mikoko") of youkai along with Tamaryu and Ran, she finally stopped lazing about in her studies, and learned how to use her fox youkai illusion magic transform into an adult.

In her adult form, she has long, straight [[black hair]] and keeps her red eyes while still usually wearing her miko outfit.  She also develops a bust that Tamaryu sometimes violently [[breast envy|envies]].

The [b]American-180[/b] is a .22 calibre [b][[submachine gun]][/b] of US origin, developed in the 1960s. A content rating will forewarn consumers as to any violent, sexual, or objectionable material presented in the show/[[video game cover|game]]/book/etc., as well as suggesting a recommended age level suitable for experiencing this content in a mature manner. Different types of media use different rating standards, although questionable material is widely encouraged to be avoided by young children.

On Danbooru, this commonly refers to explicit [[doujinshi]] that have the R-18+ notice on the [[cover page]], meaning the content is suitable for people 18 or older. The words "For Adult Only" can also count as a content rating. Another phrase seen on covers is 成人指定 ([i]seijin shitei[/i]), which means "Reserved for Adults".

h4. See also

* [[ESRB]]
* [[HowTo:Rate]]
* [[Parental Advisory]]

title: fiat_124_spider
body:
A  [[convertible]]  [[sports car]] produced by [[Fiat]] from 2016 to 2019, named for 1966-1985 Fiat 124 Sport Spider.

The modern 124 Spider was created in collaboration with [[Mazda]], using a modified version of the [[mazda mx-5 nd|ND MX-5]] platform, designated as the NE or NF platform. Due to it's connection with the MX-5 going so far as to use the same format of designation codes, the 124 Spider gained the nickname "Fiata," and is often considered an honorary MX-5 by enthusiasts.
